commit.message:
Fix test suite compatibility with Python 3.12

Replace the deprecated `unittest.TestCase.assertRaisesRegexp()` method
with `assertRaisesRegex()`.  The former is no longer present in Python
3.12, while the latter is available since Python 3.2.

Replace the deprecated `imp.reload()` function with
`importlib.reload()`.  The former module is no longer present
in Python 3.12, while `importlib.reload()` is available since
Python 3.4.

With these changes, unit tests pass with Python 3.12.0.

Fixes #153

Quick Fixup Rakefile test commands (#462)

Why This Change Is Necessary
========================================================================
There was a recent community PR that changed our tests from nosetest to
unittest, as a result Rakefile commands started failing when running
tests in a docker container on a cpair.

What These Changes Do To Address the Issue
========================================================================
Fixes up 80% of rakefile commands so that they can be used in a docker
container for easy testing.

This DOES NOT fix the scenario where we want to run a specific test.
To do so would be a deeper dive into how python modules are built so
that we can correctly structure our test commands to follow the format
of `module.TestClass.TestMethod` required by unittest library.

Side Effects Caused By This Change
========================================================================

None expected.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Relevant Links:**

  * [Unittest docs ][1]

------------------------------------------------------------------------

 [1]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.html
